{"lemma":"دِيان","slug":"دِيان","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13591"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"judge (said of God)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pious","tags":["rare"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root د ي ن (d y n). Compare Akkadian 𒁲𒋻 (dayyānum), Biblical Hebrew דַּיָּן (dayyān, “judge”), Ge'ez ዳንያ (danya) and Aramaic דינא (dayyānā)."},"ipa":["/daj.jaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13591","headword_ar":"دَيَّانٌ","root":"dyn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A requiter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who neglects not any deed, but requites it, with good"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) in this sense, with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied as an epithet to God: (S, M, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a subduer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) applied to a man in this sense; (T;) and also, in the same sense, with the article"},{"kind":"page_break","n":945},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", to God: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a judge; a ruler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"governor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) in these senses, likewise, applied to a man; and, with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", to God: (T:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a manager, a conducter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an orderer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of another. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86/","headword_ar":"دياني","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=111649#db301e","body_html":"دياني<br>عن لغة هنو أمريكا الشمالية بمعنى عزال. يستخدم للإناث."}]}}